Foam Mattress - The main reason for memory foam mattress would be to relieve pressure and pain on your back. The result is the shape of the body. Like spring mattresses, foam mattresses comprise various layers. The top layer of this type of bed is generally soft memory foam, and it gets tougher and stiffer down the layers.

Water mattresses - Water mattresses mainly reduce the pressure off the body that the typical traditional mattress can provide. Moreover it offers proper support to your spine. Water inside the water mattresses can be heated to savor the therapeutic benefits of heat. The main drawback to this kind of bed may be the water itself. A slight puncture within the mattress can be a total mess. In addition to that, every time your partner moves you, the water wave may cause you to definitely awaken from your deep sleep.

Air bed - This kind of bed are specially created for the purpose of providing comfort for your body. You may also adjust its firmness according to your decision. Air beds supply the same level of comfort as that of water mattresses. The majority of the air beds include option of latex or foam add-ons. The main drawback to air mattress is that it can hammock very easily which results in uncomfortable sleeping.

So always remember to choose a mattress that's of a good quality that fixes well within your financial allowance as well as a comfortable one.